5000|$|A {{sidereal year}} (from Latin sidus [...] "asterism, star") {{is the time}} taken by the Earth to orbit the Sun once {{with respect to the}} <b>fixed</b> <b>stars.</b> Hence it is also the time taken for the Sun to return to the same {{position}} with respect to the <b>fixed</b> <b>stars</b> after apparently travelling once around the ecliptic. It equals 365.25636 SI days for the J2000.0 epoch.|$|R
